FBIS4-65941 "drweu102_j_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Ruling Coalition Gains Chamber Chairmanships Ruling Coalition Gains Chamber Chairmanships LD2505183294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1548 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505183294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Italian BFN [Text] The ruling coalition has gained the chairmanships of the Chamber of Deputies committees. The outcome of the voting was a foregone conclusion, except for the the foreign affairs committee, where Mirko Tremaglia from the National Alliance won over Emma Bonino from the Radical Party by a single vote. Following is the full list of chairmen of the parliamentary committees: Gustavo Selva (constitutional affairs) and Paolo Agostinacchio (finance) from the National Alliance; Paolo Bampo (defense), Roberto Calderoli (social affairs), Marco Sartori (labor), Alberto Paolo Lembo (agriculture), and Francesco Formenti (environment) from the Northern League; Tiziana Maiolo (justice), Silvio Liotta (budget), Vittorio Sgarbi (culture), and Alessandro Rubino from Forza Italia; and Sante Perticaro (transport) from the Christian Democrat Center.
